02:28.685 --> 02:30.550
(loud bang)

02:30.550 --> 02:31.773
I'm recording this!

02:41.590 --> 02:42.610
Jacob.

02:42.610 --> 02:44.080
It was seven pairs.

02:44.080 --> 02:47.120
- [Jacob] I didn't
touch your stupid shoes.

02:47.120 --> 02:48.070
- What?

02:48.070 --> 02:51.070
- [Jacob] (crying) I didn't
touch your stupid shoes.

02:51.070 --> 02:51.903
- Very funny.

02:55.150 --> 02:55.983
What did you throw?

02:55.983 --> 02:57.580
What smashed?

02:57.580 --> 02:58.413
- Nothing.

03:00.160 --> 03:01.653
You're the one "monstering out", okay?

03:01.653 --> 03:03.630
Just take a bath or something...

03:09.828 --> 03:12.578
(mouse clicking)

03:15.440 --> 03:18.310
Welcome to the worst town in America;

03:18.310 --> 03:19.600
Parma, Ohio.
- Hey.

03:20.840 --> 03:25.080
I am here interviewing the
aloof new boy of the school,

03:25.080 --> 03:27.513
Jacob Bell, everyone!

03:28.390 --> 03:29.570
Save "hi", Jacob.

03:29.570 --> 03:30.673
Stop it!

03:37.290 --> 03:38.483
- My name is Abbey.

03:39.420 --> 03:42.400
I live in Parma, Ohio--

03:42.400 --> 03:43.970
Oh shit!

03:43.970 --> 03:45.113
I'm thirty.

03:46.800 --> 03:48.611
Well, mid 30s.

03:48.611 --> 03:49.863
Mid to late 30s.

03:50.910 --> 03:51.850
Not 40...

03:52.773 --> 03:54.193
Definitely not 40.

04:03.330 --> 04:04.423
My name is Abbey.

04:05.780 --> 04:07.003
I'm 42 years old.

04:09.020 --> 04:10.023
I'm a single mom.

04:11.570 --> 04:16.000
My son, Jacob, he just
turned 16, which is...

04:17.166 --> 04:19.692
Well, that's a handful
for any kind of mom.

04:22.750 --> 04:23.800
The thing is...

04:26.010 --> 04:27.130
Jacob is...

04:30.790 --> 04:32.280
I think he is, anyway...

04:37.660 --> 04:39.090
I think he's going to...

04:45.114 --> 04:46.364
This is stupid.

04:49.500 --> 04:50.810
- [Greg] Dude, we gotta get outta here.

04:50.810 --> 04:52.310
We're gonna get arrested, bro.

04:55.980 --> 04:56.930
What are you doing?

04:59.460 --> 05:00.573
- Natural selection.

05:01.870 --> 05:03.580
- [Greg] Oh, don't even
play like that, bro.

05:03.580 --> 05:06.295
You're gonna cause a fucking
accident or something.

05:06.295 --> 05:07.160
Oh fuck!

05:07.160 --> 05:08.792
Shit!

05:08.792 --> 05:10.825
Get the fuck out of here, bro!

05:10.825 --> 05:12.158
Dude go, go, go!

05:20.521 --> 05:21.771
- Look at this.

05:25.360 --> 05:27.823
If this was just for
his geometry assignment,

05:31.800 --> 05:33.393
why would he draw himself, huh?

05:37.317 --> 05:39.623
"To demonstrate scale" my ass.

05:42.594 --> 05:43.744
And here, look at this.

05:48.760 --> 05:51.160
Why would a 14 year old
boy even have this, huh?

05:57.931 --> 05:59.860
What kind of kid wants
to turn his pellet gun

05:59.860 --> 06:01.123
into an automatic weapon?

06:04.160 --> 06:06.520
Bump stocks were not invented
for fucking air guns,

06:06.520 --> 06:07.510
I'll tell you that.

06:12.610 --> 06:13.870
I'm sorry, I just...

06:15.840 --> 06:17.990
I don't understand why there
aren't more resources out there

06:17.990 --> 06:19.830
to deal with this kind of thing.

06:19.830 --> 06:21.293
I reported him two years ago.

06:22.420 --> 06:24.130
And yeah, they launched an investigation,

06:24.130 --> 06:26.437
put Jacob under surveillance.

06:26.437 --> 06:28.165
"Your son provided a rational explanation

06:28.165 --> 06:29.857
"for every offense."

06:31.180 --> 06:32.280
That's what they said.

06:33.377 --> 06:34.917
"Rational explanation."

06:36.300 --> 06:37.350
Now I'm the bad guy

06:37.350 --> 06:39.780
'cause Jacob served time
in a diversion program

06:42.508 --> 06:43.458
and we had to move.

06:45.748 --> 06:46.581
Again.

06:49.893 --> 06:51.160
He's already in therapy,

06:51.160 --> 06:53.247
so couldn't blame me for that one.

07:00.490 --> 07:02.410
My mom spent a shit ton in legal fees

07:02.410 --> 07:04.043
to get all this stuff back, too.

07:04.970 --> 07:06.993
God forbid it goes on his record.

07:07.930 --> 07:08.805
She's like,

07:08.805 --> 07:09.940
"You don't wanna be the boy
who cried 'wolf', do you?"

07:09.940 --> 07:10.903
I'm like, "No, mom.

07:11.977 --> 07:12.817
"I don't."

07:15.330 --> 07:18.660
By the way, the boy who cried wolf

07:20.980 --> 07:22.443
got eaten by the fuckin' wolf.

07:29.580 --> 07:31.550
- We were talking about how
to get more bang for your buck

07:31.550 --> 07:33.400
out of everyone's favorite AR-15.

07:33.400 --> 07:34.930
And with you guys shooting the .223s

07:34.930 --> 07:37.926
or the 5.56s, everyone knows--

07:37.926 --> 07:40.676
(video skipping)

07:41.870 --> 07:44.753
- [Abbey] Sleeping Jacob
is my favorite Jacob.

07:46.240 --> 07:50.440
He had almost a two hour tantrum.

07:50.440 --> 07:51.943
Worked himself into a fit.

07:53.410 --> 07:54.523
Now he's sleeping.

07:55.750 --> 07:57.736
Honey, I don't think
you can climb on that!

07:57.736 --> 07:59.800
- [Dad] There are all those
babies living in there.

07:59.800 --> 08:00.633
- [Abbey] That's somebody's--

08:00.633 --> 08:01.859
That's a birdhouse.

08:01.859 --> 08:02.692
No, no!

08:02.692 --> 08:04.104
Babies, no!

08:04.104 --> 08:05.963
- [Dad] There are baby birds in there.

08:05.963 --> 08:07.796
- [Abbey] Let go, now!

08:08.954 --> 08:09.977
- What?

08:09.977 --> 08:11.394
- [Abbey] Let go.

08:12.230 --> 08:14.970
- [Dad] That's why that bird
is swooping at your head.

08:14.970 --> 08:16.159
- [Abbey] They're very upset.

08:16.159 --> 08:17.530
- [Mom] Walk away!

08:21.702 --> 08:25.869
(rap music plays through earbuds)

08:27.910 --> 08:29.763
- You know that's illegal, right?

08:30.800 --> 08:32.669
- [Abbey] The light's red.

08:32.669 --> 08:34.270
- What are you recording me for?

08:35.538 --> 08:36.371
- [Abbey] I want to capture

08:36.371 --> 08:38.070
that miraculous transformation you make.

08:38.980 --> 08:40.270
When you're alone in the car with mom

08:40.270 --> 08:42.270
to when you're not alone
in the car with mom.

08:42.270 --> 08:44.280
- For what; for who?

08:50.380 --> 08:53.410
Hey, Detective Kelly, remember me?

08:53.410 --> 08:55.350
Mom's freaking out again.

08:55.350 --> 08:56.410
- Knock it off.

08:56.410 --> 08:58.168
- She came home totally hammered

08:58.168 --> 09:01.730
and she cut up all her shoes.

09:01.730 --> 09:03.610
She's probably gonna say I did it,

09:03.610 --> 09:04.810
but just for the record.

09:05.730 --> 09:06.563
Later.

09:07.880 --> 09:08.713
- [Abbey] You're disgusting.

09:08.713 --> 09:10.433
Look me in the eye and say that again.

09:11.870 --> 09:13.540
- You were drunk.

09:13.540 --> 09:15.260
You cut up your shoes.

09:15.260 --> 09:16.093
Again.

09:17.492 --> 09:18.490
(car horn blares)

09:18.490 --> 09:19.973
Fucking go already.

09:23.910 --> 09:26.320
- Well, he knows I'm recording, so.

09:26.320 --> 09:28.520
Technically, he's still
in the car with mom.

09:29.900 --> 09:32.663
This may be the "other Jacob" emerging.

09:34.150 --> 09:35.303
The fake Jacob.

09:37.397 --> 09:42.110
The thing is, he doesn't
fit the profile of a...

09:43.090 --> 09:46.810
I mean he has friends
and gets good grades.

09:46.810 --> 09:47.993
His teachers like him.

09:49.340 --> 09:51.360
Except from that one
jerky science teacher,

09:51.360 --> 09:53.003
everyone loves the fake Jacob.

09:54.333 --> 09:56.720
(bell rings)

09:56.720 --> 10:00.043
To be honest, every time
they tell me I'm wrong,

10:01.151 --> 10:02.770
that I'm exaggerating his symptoms,

10:02.770 --> 10:05.973
I feel this enormous sense of relief.

10:07.280 --> 10:09.963
I mean, what if it is me?

10:11.611 --> 10:13.023
What if Jacob is okay?

10:16.087 --> 10:18.653
"Psychosomatic projection",
I think they call it.

10:19.780 --> 10:21.890
It's when you experience
this trauma as a kid,

10:21.890 --> 10:24.690
this extreme fucking trauma

10:24.690 --> 10:28.400
and you project that on your husband,

10:28.400 --> 10:30.203
your kid, your parents.

10:32.540 --> 10:34.340
Then I think, "What if it's not me?"

10:36.760 --> 10:38.023
What if it's genetic?

10:40.490 --> 10:43.990
Sometimes when I look in
his eyes I get this replay,

10:43.990 --> 10:46.723
this instant fucking replay of Jerry,

10:47.559 --> 10:50.807
and I imagine him in that
Mustang with his sawed off--

10:50.807 --> 10:51.640
(banging on window)

10:51.640 --> 10:52.790
- [School Officer] Pickup
and drop-off only, ma'am.

10:52.790 --> 10:53.623
- [Abbey] Thank you!

10:53.623 --> 10:54.456
Sorry.

10:55.930 --> 10:57.143
This is his room.

11:04.260 --> 11:05.730
When he's not at school,

11:05.730 --> 11:08.083
this is where he spends most of his time.

11:10.870 --> 11:11.963
All of his time.

11:14.160 --> 11:16.800
This is Adolf.

11:16.800 --> 11:17.633
Hi!

11:18.530 --> 11:20.903
Last one died, so this is Adolf Junior.

11:21.868 --> 11:23.853
Or Adolf Junior Jr., maybe.

11:27.271 --> 11:28.223
As you can see,

11:30.015 --> 11:31.530
he plays a lot of video games.

11:31.530 --> 11:33.493
I think that's pretty normal.

11:34.638 --> 11:35.633
I mean,

11:37.770 --> 11:38.713
is that normal?

11:40.330 --> 11:42.280
Spend five, six hours a day?

11:42.280 --> 11:43.510
I don't know, just...

11:44.750 --> 11:45.763
Shooting people.

11:48.320 --> 11:49.483
People say it's normal.

11:51.330 --> 11:52.163
People.

11:56.060 --> 11:59.073
What's not normal, is this.

12:03.531 --> 12:05.480
(locked door handle rattles)

12:05.480 --> 12:06.433
Are you kidding me?

12:06.433 --> 12:07.266
Jesus.

12:08.710 --> 12:10.760
- Talk American.

12:10.760 --> 12:13.064
- [Girlfriend] Would you like
me better if I was British?

12:13.064 --> 12:14.100
(Jacob gags)

12:14.100 --> 12:14.933
- No.

12:17.010 --> 12:17.843
- [Girlfriend] Hey, you've gotta help me

12:17.843 --> 12:18.923
with my science project.

12:20.257 --> 12:21.673
- It's so easy.

12:21.673 --> 12:23.923
- [Girlfriend] It's
not easy for all of us.

12:25.254 --> 12:26.990
Aren't you supposed to be
really smart or something?

12:26.990 --> 12:27.940
What are you doing?

12:29.561 --> 12:30.950
(Jacob imitates gunshot)

12:30.950 --> 12:32.213
You're such an asshole!

12:33.529 --> 12:34.362
- [Jacob] (Laughing) Whatever.

12:34.362 --> 12:36.000
He's fucking old anyway.

12:36.000 --> 12:36.833
- [Girlfriend] Why?

12:36.833 --> 12:38.340
You think we should just
kill off all old people?

12:38.340 --> 12:39.386
- Yes!

12:39.386 --> 12:40.841
That is a good idea!

12:40.841 --> 12:41.676
- [Girlfriend] Oh Whatever.
- [Jacob] See?

12:41.676 --> 12:44.240
You're already halfway done
with your science project.

12:44.240 --> 12:45.300
- Fucking jaw off...

12:46.220 --> 12:47.870
- [Abbey] Say what you just said.

12:49.810 --> 12:50.643
I'm serious.

12:50.643 --> 12:51.790
Say what you just said.

12:51.790 --> 12:52.623
- Stop already.

12:54.140 --> 12:55.230
- [Abbey] Knock it off.

12:55.230 --> 12:56.240
- Chill, mom, seriously.

12:56.240 --> 12:57.073
- [Abbey] Let go.

12:57.073 --> 12:57.906
Ow, you're hurting me.

12:57.906 --> 12:59.187
- I'm not even touching you.

13:00.730 --> 13:01.563
- Jacob!

13:08.790 --> 13:10.940
See, that's exactly
what I'm talking about.

13:18.610 --> 13:23.610
Okay, I got this when he was
around two of wetting the bed

13:25.620 --> 13:26.853
with his diapers on.

13:30.970 --> 13:33.820
I caught him taking them
off, pissing the bed,

13:33.820 --> 13:35.720
and putting his diapers back on again.

13:36.910 --> 13:38.323
Little creep.

13:40.340 --> 13:42.253
Shit, where's the charging thingy?

13:45.503 --> 13:46.490
(straw sipping)

13:46.490 --> 13:47.323
Testing.

13:55.510 --> 13:56.400
All right...

13:57.910 --> 14:01.443
Okay, so it's May 4th, 2018, by the way.

14:02.420 --> 14:04.020
Jacob should be home any minute.

14:04.920 --> 14:07.330
If his PlayStation isn't back in his room,

14:07.330 --> 14:08.827
