14:09.809 --> 14:10.642
That's what he said,

14:10.642 --> 14:12.387
"I'll rip your fucking jaw off."

14:15.440 --> 14:16.273
Look, I know.

14:16.273 --> 14:18.500
I know I'm not handling
this well; I know that.

14:19.510 --> 14:20.990
He can't keep breaking my shit.

14:20.990 --> 14:22.490
He's not a little kid anymore.

14:24.887 --> 14:27.180
I know, I know...

14:29.687 --> 14:30.623
I'm a mom.

14:33.900 --> 14:34.857
I'm a mom--

14:37.904 --> 14:40.821
(front door opens)

14:45.330 --> 14:46.163
Hey.

14:59.120 --> 14:59.953
- Mom...

15:01.570 --> 15:02.670
What the hell is this?

15:04.010 --> 15:06.250
- Sign it, and I will give
you your PlayStation back.

15:06.250 --> 15:07.450
- Are you fucking joking?

15:07.450 --> 15:08.647
- Lose the attitude, Jacob.

15:08.647 --> 15:11.610
You can pay me back a
little bit at a time.

15:19.273 --> 15:21.460
(phone buzzes)

15:21.460 --> 15:22.620
Why are you calling me?

15:22.620 --> 15:24.127
- Why do you think?

15:24.127 --> 15:25.660
- I'm not recording you.

15:25.660 --> 15:26.493
- Where is it?

15:36.200 --> 15:37.550
- It's not in there, Jacob.

15:39.215 --> 15:41.570
- Where the fuck is my PlayStation?

15:41.570 --> 15:43.060
I told you; I warned you!

15:43.060 --> 15:46.523
- And I told you if you sign
it, you will get it back.

15:52.340 --> 15:55.113
Jacob, don't do that.

15:58.070 --> 16:01.590
God, if you could just not
be a little shit for once...

16:01.590 --> 16:03.380
Okay, you know what?

16:03.380 --> 16:04.213
I'm out.

16:04.213 --> 16:05.460
I'm not doing this with you.

16:07.011 --> 16:08.227
Okay--

16:08.227 --> 16:09.207
Jacob!

16:09.207 --> 16:10.040
Stop it now!

16:10.040 --> 16:10.873
(Jacob yells)

16:10.873 --> 16:11.706
No!

16:15.896 --> 16:20.229
(thrashing comes from Jacob's room)

17:27.714 --> 17:28.715
- I'm sorry.

17:34.773 --> 17:35.606
- I know.

18:04.970 --> 18:09.933
- [Jacob] So, what was the
worst day of your life?

18:11.620 --> 18:12.640
- Jesus...

18:15.070 --> 18:17.423
Probably the day my stepmom moved in.

18:18.710 --> 18:19.543
- [Jacob] Why?

18:21.030 --> 18:21.863
- I don't know.

18:21.863 --> 18:23.590
Because it just meant my
mom wasn't coming home

18:23.590 --> 18:26.483
and it made everything like really final.

18:29.920 --> 18:31.040
And she sucks.

18:31.040 --> 18:32.683
She's the worst.

18:34.860 --> 18:36.702
- [Jacob] Want me to just kill her?

18:36.702 --> 18:39.730
- Yeah, Jacob, fantastic idea.

18:39.730 --> 18:40.563
Thank you.

18:42.980 --> 18:46.110
So, is it true you moved here

18:46.110 --> 18:48.250
because you got kicked out of Riverside?

18:48.250 --> 18:49.083
- Is that your question?

18:49.083 --> 18:50.280
- [Girlfriend] Yeah.

18:50.280 --> 18:52.008
- You and everybody else.

18:52.008 --> 18:54.175
Ask me something original.

18:55.884 --> 18:57.620
- [Girlfriend] Okay,

18:57.620 --> 18:59.773
what's with the long sleeves all the time?

19:00.920 --> 19:03.350
- What's with all the
fuckin' push-up bras?

19:03.350 --> 19:04.820
- [Girlfriend] Whoa, it's truth or dare.

19:04.820 --> 19:06.030
You have to answer.

19:06.030 --> 19:06.863
C'mon--

19:06.863 --> 19:07.832
- Stop it.

19:07.832 --> 19:09.587
It's a stupid game.

19:09.587 --> 19:11.920
- Okay, and this is his Risperidone.

19:11.920 --> 19:14.580
It's kinda like an antidepressant.

19:14.580 --> 19:19.580
Well, actually it's an
antipsychotic but that's a bit much.

19:20.290 --> 19:22.040
He takes that with the Carbamazepine,

19:22.040 --> 19:23.524
which is for seizures.

19:23.524 --> 19:24.580
Well, that's wrong.

19:24.580 --> 19:27.280
I mean, it's not wrong, it's
just not why he takes it.

19:28.760 --> 19:33.720
Adderall, 15 milligrams
of this every morning.

19:33.720 --> 19:36.647
For his, y'know--

19:36.647 --> 19:38.133
His attention deficit.

19:39.230 --> 19:40.640
Can you hear me now?

19:40.640 --> 19:42.760
- I can hear you just fine.

19:42.760 --> 19:44.360
Your face just keeps freezing up.

19:44.360 --> 19:46.700
Why can't we just talk on the telephone?

19:46.700 --> 19:47.810
- You look fine, mom.

19:47.810 --> 19:49.113
- Yeah, look at my hair!

19:49.113 --> 19:51.290
Let me get some lipstick on.

19:51.290 --> 19:53.100
- Listen, mom, Jacob's gonna be home soon.

19:53.100 --> 19:53.933
Could you just--

19:53.933 --> 19:54.766
- I'm listening, honey.

19:54.766 --> 19:57.350
I'm just getting my lipstick thingy.

19:57.350 --> 19:59.580
- He's having the tantrums again.

19:59.580 --> 20:01.230
The other day, he pinned
me up against a wall

20:01.230 --> 20:02.840
and I couldn't get out
from underneath him.

20:02.840 --> 20:04.250
- Well why would you let him do that?

20:04.250 --> 20:06.623
Boys aren't supposed to
wrestle with their mothers.

20:06.623 --> 20:07.990
That's what fathers are for.

20:07.990 --> 20:08.823
- No, don't.

20:08.823 --> 20:10.167
Don't do that.

20:10.167 --> 20:11.000
- What?

20:11.000 --> 20:12.210
What'd I do?

20:12.210 --> 20:13.260
I didn't even say his name.

20:13.260 --> 20:14.370
- We weren't wrestling, mom.

20:14.370 --> 20:15.617
He was angry, okay?

20:15.617 --> 20:17.000
- Well he's a teenager.

20:17.000 --> 20:19.420
Teenagers are moody, especially boys.

20:19.420 --> 20:20.253
All those hormones.

20:20.253 --> 20:21.610
- No, this wasn't hormones, mom.

20:21.610 --> 20:25.697
His eyes, they were blank, detached.

20:28.050 --> 20:29.030
He looked like...

20:30.120 --> 20:31.313
He looked like Jerry.

20:33.131 --> 20:35.708
- I don't wanna do this again, Abbey.

20:35.708 --> 20:36.980
- I know you don't want to do this, mom.

20:36.980 --> 20:38.010
I don't want to do this either,

20:38.010 --> 20:39.470
but what if they were wrong?

20:39.470 --> 20:41.207
I mean, mom, if you could have
done something to stop Jerry,

20:41.207 --> 20:43.070
you would have done it, right?

20:43.070 --> 20:45.180
- You don't even know
what you're talking about!

20:45.180 --> 20:47.020
You were a baby.

20:47.020 --> 20:48.469
- I was twelve.

20:48.469 --> 20:50.240
- I don't wanna talk about this.

20:50.240 --> 20:52.300
- Mom, there must have
been some kind of signs.

20:52.300 --> 20:54.260
You must have noticed something.

20:54.260 --> 20:56.717
- I can't believe this is happening again.

20:56.717 --> 20:59.040
Are you taking your medications?

20:59.040 --> 21:01.592
- Yes, of course I'm taking my medication.

21:01.592 --> 21:03.320
- But they're not helping?

21:03.320 --> 21:04.500
- They're not helping Jacob.

21:04.500 --> 21:05.940
Jesus, mom.

21:05.940 --> 21:08.070
- Okay, what did you find?

21:08.070 --> 21:09.655
Did you find something?

21:09.655 --> 21:11.480
- No, I don't...

21:11.480 --> 21:13.900
He's cutting up my shoes again

21:13.900 --> 21:17.310
and the nicks on his arms.

21:17.310 --> 21:18.550
- New nicks?

21:18.550 --> 21:19.383
- No.

21:19.383 --> 21:20.216
I don't know.

21:21.080 --> 21:23.690
I mean, mom, what if he hurts me?

21:23.690 --> 21:25.150
What if he hurts someone else?

21:25.150 --> 21:28.250
- Abigail, the things you're saying...

21:28.250 --> 21:29.453
What you're implying,

21:30.290 --> 21:31.630
it's very serious.

21:31.630 --> 21:33.320
- I know!

21:33.320 --> 21:35.650
- I don't think you should tell anyone.

21:35.650 --> 21:37.380
- I'm telling you, mom.

21:37.380 --> 21:39.970
- And I believed you the last time,

21:39.970 --> 21:41.722
all the way to the end.

21:41.722 --> 21:44.140
Universities look for that kind of stuff.

21:44.140 --> 21:45.847
I know they say they don't, but they do.

21:45.847 --> 21:48.040
And all those medications you have him on,

21:48.040 --> 21:49.040
they all go on his record.

21:49.040 --> 21:50.250
I warned you about that;

21:50.250 --> 21:53.570
If something bad happens
and Jacob takes the fall.

21:53.570 --> 21:55.974
- No, mom, I'm trying
to prevent something bad

21:55.974 --> 21:57.700
from happening.

21:57.700 --> 21:59.192
- Maybe you should talk to Howard.

21:59.192 --> 22:00.025
(front door opens)

22:00.025 --> 22:00.858
You remember Howard?

22:00.858 --> 22:01.760
Howard's a vault.

22:01.760 --> 22:02.620
- 'Kay, you know what, mom?

22:02.620 --> 22:03.860
I gotta go.

22:03.860 --> 22:05.200
I'll call you later.

22:05.200 --> 22:09.290
- Abigail, you're not sure, are you?

22:09.290 --> 22:11.090
- I'll call you later.

22:11.090 --> 22:12.600
- Call who later?

22:12.600 --> 22:13.433
- [Nana] Is that Jacob?

22:13.433 --> 22:14.810
Honey, is that you?

22:14.810 --> 22:15.833
- Nana?

22:18.237 --> 22:19.671
What up, Nana?

22:19.671 --> 22:21.930
- Oh my god, you're gigantic!

22:21.930 --> 22:23.908
So handsome!

22:23.908 --> 22:25.540
- Aw, c'mon now, Nana.

22:25.540 --> 22:27.478
You say that to all the boys!

22:27.478 --> 22:30.070
- [Nana] What a horrible face.

22:30.070 --> 22:31.370
Uncross your eyes!

22:31.370 --> 22:32.590
- Nana, my eyes are stuck!

22:32.590 --> 22:34.270
I'm gonna be cross-eyed forever!

22:34.270 --> 22:35.103
Oh my god!

22:35.103 --> 22:35.977
Nana, no!

22:35.977 --> 22:36.810
(imitates gunshot)

22:36.810 --> 22:40.480
(Nana laughs merrily)

22:40.480 --> 22:42.730
Hey, thanks for the
birthday cash you sent.

22:42.730 --> 22:43.870
That was awesome.

22:43.870 --> 22:45.277
- [Nana] I wanted to get you a present,

22:45.277 --> 22:47.310
but you're so hard to shop for these days.

22:47.310 --> 22:48.480
- Oh, so get this.

22:48.480 --> 22:50.330
Urban has these killer combat boots.

22:50.330 --> 22:52.200
You can order them online and everything.

22:52.200 --> 22:53.140
- [Nana] Urban...

22:53.140 --> 22:55.070
Urban what?

22:55.070 --> 22:57.200
- Here, just type in this website, ready?

22:57.200 --> 22:58.313
- Oh no, no, no.

22:58.313 --> 22:59.146
(chuckling) I can't.

22:59.146 --> 23:01.480
Just buy the boots with the
birthday present I sent.

23:01.480 --> 23:03.610
- What if you set me up with a credit card

23:03.610 --> 23:05.640
and I'll hook you up with
a dope-ass Snapchat account

23:05.640 --> 23:08.200
where you can see what I'm
doing like every five minutes.

23:08.200 --> 23:09.956
- Don't listen to him, mom.

23:09.956 --> 23:11.257
- Yeah, you may have gotten bigger

23:11.257 --> 23:13.190
but you haven't changed a bit!

23:13.190 --> 23:14.680
- Is that a yes?

23:14.680 --> 23:17.630
- No, you can get him a
credit card when he's 18.

23:17.630 --> 23:18.463
- [Nana] Deal.

23:18.463 --> 23:20.093
But I better put a limit on it.

23:22.810 --> 23:24.310
- Did you just hang up on her?

23:25.723 --> 23:27.253
Why would you do that?

23:27.253 --> 23:28.961
- When I'm 18?

23:28.961 --> 23:29.794
Please.

23:40.021 --> 23:44.354
(rap music plays from Jacob's room)

23:46.078 --> 23:48.828
(door squealing)

23:49.990 --> 23:50.913
- [Abbey] Jacob?

23:55.080 --> 23:57.541
Jacob, I know you're down here.

23:57.541 --> 23:59.791
(rustling)

24:08.010 --> 24:09.073
Jacob, honey?

24:10.871 --> 24:11.704
- Ah!

24:11.704 --> 24:13.720
- [Abbey] Oh my god!

24:13.720 --> 24:14.880
Jesus, you scared...

24:17.907 --> 24:18.870
God damn it...

24:21.853 --> 24:23.410
Are you in my robe?

24:23.410 --> 24:25.465
- [Voicemail] Shipping
out your Eczema cream,

24:25.465 --> 24:26.298
but we couldn't retail your--

24:26.298 --> 24:28.273
(door squeals)

24:28.273 --> 24:30.550
For the cosmetic moisturizing gloves

24:30.550 --> 24:33.200
because it looks like your
mom's credit card expired.

24:34.342 --> 24:35.845
- He install this himself?

24:35.845 --> 24:37.010
- I don't know, I guess he must have.

24:37.010 --> 24:39.180
- Man, you got a smart kid on your hands.

24:39.180 --> 24:41.520
- Yeah, thanks.

24:41.520 --> 24:42.780
I really appreciate it.

24:42.780 --> 24:43.613
- Yeah.

24:59.293 --> 25:01.143
- God, it smells like crap in here.

25:02.130 --> 25:04.030
Like burnt rubber or something...

25:11.890 --> 25:14.010
His baby pictures.

25:14.010 --> 25:16.163
He was six when he started drawing these.

25:17.300 --> 25:18.610
As you can see, they've been rescued

25:18.610 --> 25:20.283
from the trash a few times.

25:23.030 --> 25:24.623
I asked him if that was me;

25:26.089 --> 25:28.173
if that was Jacob in Mommy's belly.

25:29.610 --> 25:31.943
He said no, it was Nana;

25:33.170 --> 25:34.823
he didn't know who the baby was.

25:37.117 --> 25:42.063
I mean, if that's Nana,
then who's the baby?

25:44.490 --> 25:46.190
I never told him about my brother.

25:49.540 --> 25:50.993
I never told him about Jerry.

25:54.330 --> 25:55.163
Anyway...

26:05.130 --> 26:06.813
Oh, nice, Jacob.

26:08.910 --> 26:11.211
Oh, Jesus...

26:11.211 --> 26:12.443
Shit.

26:46.520 --> 26:48.350
Oh my god!

26:48.350 --> 26:49.793
Shit, shit, shit!

26:50.730 --> 26:53.283
No, c'mon, get back in.

26:54.508 --> 26:57.283
He feeds these to Adolf, that's all.

27:12.948 --> 27:13.865
What the...

27:18.425 --> 27:19.675
Jesus Christ...

27:25.163 --> 27:26.413
Holy shit.

27:31.974 --> 27:34.474
What the fuck did he do to it?

27:40.120 --> 27:41.080
Oh, Jesus...

27:43.030 --> 27:44.618
I suppose you're gonna
find a rational explanation

27:44.618 --> 27:45.833
for this too, huh?

27:48.340 --> 27:49.463
My name is Abbey.

27:50.460 --> 27:51.723
I'm 42 years old.

27:52.580 --> 27:53.583
I'm a single mom.

27:55.490 --> 28:00.490
I think my 16 year old
son is a psychopath.

28:03.757 --> 28:05.507
I'm not trying to prove it anymore.

28:06.760 --> 28:09.023
By the time, I'm sure it'll be too late.

28:10.664 --> 28:13.014
I'm not doing this for
the authorities, either.

28:13.962 --> 28:15.740
No, I'm...

28:15.740 --> 28:17.353
I'm making these videos for you.

28:19.323 --> 28:20.923
For all you other moms out there

28:22.496 --> 28:25.793
who know deep down that
your kid is a bad kid.

28:28.069 --> 28:29.583
But you still love him.

28:33.210 --> 28:34.463
Because he's your son.

28:37.918 --> 28:39.268
We're gonna look for signs.

28:41.350 --> 28:43.450
We're gonna look for patterns, you and me,

28:44.520 --> 28:46.320
and together, we're gonna figure out

28:47.710 --> 28:48.990
if you are "that" mom

28:51.032 --> 28:52.563
and if your kid is "that" kid.

28:55.466 --> 28:56.780
I mean, let's face it.

28:58.837 --> 29:00.053
If I'm wrong,

29:02.900 --> 29:05.150
if these videos never
see the light of day...

29:06.900 --> 29:11.003
But if I'm right, if you're watching this,

29:14.540 --> 29:17.573
(laughs) I'm already dead.

29:18.929 --> 29:23.130
(speculative piano plays)

29:23.130 --> 29:25.190
I'm not saying therapists can't help,

29:25.190 --> 29:26.810
but do your own research.

29:26.810 --> 29:28.090
And not just on the internet either;

29:28.090 --> 29:30.493
there are books, interviews,
published studies.

29:31.370 --> 29:33.010
Okay, so there's the usual stuff;

29:33.010 --> 29:36.670
the lack of empathy, antisocial behavior,

29:36.670 --> 29:37.670
pathological lying.

29:37.670 --> 29:39.200
That's a big one.

29:39.200 --> 29:40.710
But then there are the more subtle signs

29:40.710 --> 29:45.017
like chronic conspiracy
theories or racism.

29:46.510 --> 29:48.120
That's a big one.

29:48.120 --> 29:50.843
NPV, Narcissistic Personality Disorder.

29:52.280 --> 29:54.700
I hope you're writing this down.

29:54.700 --> 29:57.192
I guess you could always just rewind.

29:57.192 --> 29:58.460
(off key piano notes)

29:58.460 --> 29:59.293
By the way,

30:00.977 --> 30:03.655
if you're not a mom with a troubled kid

30:03.655 --> 30:04.905
and you're watching this,

30:07.065 --> 30:08.265
you're a psychopath too.

30:10.530 --> 30:11.993
Have some fucking respect.

30:13.890 --> 30:14.723
- [Greg] You're crazy.

30:14.723 --> 30:15.840
I don't know, man.

30:15.840 --> 30:17.800
- This is Jacob Bell

30:17.800 --> 30:22.170
coming to you live with the
electro shock challenge.

30:22.170 --> 30:24.190
We got a electric dog collar

30:24.190 --> 30:26.430
that I stole from my stupid neighbor

30:28.050 --> 30:33.050
and this should pack a pretty
heavy punch to my jugular.

30:33.060 --> 30:34.830
So let's try some levels.

30:34.830 --> 30:37.960
Let's start with...

30:37.960 --> 30:38.793
Eight.

30:38.793 --> 30:39.920
- [Greg] An eight?

30:39.920 --> 30:40.753
Oh shit, man.

30:40.753 --> 30:41.750
You are out of your mind!

30:41.750 --> 30:42.844
- Pussy.

30:42.844 --> 30:43.710
(laughing)

30:43.710 --> 30:44.714
Three--

30:44.714 --> 30:45.547
- [Greg] I don't know about this, man.

30:45.547 --> 30:47.119
- Two, one.

30:47.119 --> 30:48.853
(electric collar buzzing)

30:48.853 --> 30:50.152
- Oh shit!

30:50.152 --> 30:51.130
(Jacob breathing heavily)

30:51.130 --> 30:53.849
Bro, are you all right?

30:53.849 --> 30:56.180
- That was fucking awesome!

30:58.743 --> 31:01.100
- What kind of supplies.

31:01.100 --> 31:03.770
- Well, the science lab is missing

31:04.670 --> 31:09.670
some specimen pins,
closures, sodium hydroxide,

31:11.580 --> 31:13.810
a container of formaldehyde.

31:13.810 --> 31:15.760
- Great, so if I hadn't stopped by today

31:15.760 --> 31:19.320
I'd just have to guess
why my son got detention?

31:19.320 --> 31:20.400
- We sent the letter.

31:20.400 --> 31:22.620
- I told you that's not my signature.

31:22.620 --> 31:24.460
- Listen, is this gonna go on his record.

31:24.460 --> 31:25.720
- His record?

31:25.720 --> 31:28.493
No, this stays in his
file until he graduates.

31:29.580 --> 31:30.413
- I don't know why

31:30.413 --> 31:32.400
you guys are still
teaching dissection anyway.

31:32.400 --> 31:34.860
It was banned in the Riverside
district two years ago.

31:34.860 --> 31:36.610
- It's not about dissection, really.

31:36.610 --> 31:38.860
It's more about electric
muscle stimulation;

31:38.860 --> 31:41.440
teaching the students
about the human body.

31:41.440 --> 31:43.010
- Great.

31:43.010 --> 31:46.240
- Look, Jacob is a very gifted student.

31:46.240 --> 31:48.210
I wouldn't worry so much
about what's in his file,

31:48.210 --> 31:51.020
just put it into conversation with him.

31:51.020 --> 31:53.401
Transparency is key
with this sort of thing.

31:53.401 --> 31:54.339
- Of course.

31:54.339 --> 31:56.780
I'm so sorry to have barged in.

31:56.780 --> 31:58.580
- Which parking lot are you in?

31:59.995 --> 32:02.540
- [Abbey] Where are you going?

32:02.540 --> 32:05.383
Well, he's not going to
Greg's house, that's obvious.

32:12.166 --> 32:14.416
What is he doing over here?

32:29.292 --> 32:30.125
What?

32:32.073 --> 32:33.049
Oh no...

32:33.049 --> 32:33.882
No, no.

32:38.365 --> 32:42.290
I mean, it's not like he can get a gun.

32:42.290 --> 32:43.123
Right?

32:58.723 --> 33:01.573
All right, well, it's on.

33:02.510 --> 33:05.973
I can't figure out how to
do the "record" thingy.

33:10.040 --> 33:13.863
Spy camera number one; kitchen cam.

33:18.260 --> 33:22.460
Okay, so kitchen cam is
housed in this nifty little

33:23.580 --> 33:25.940
electrical outlet thingy.

33:25.940 --> 33:29.053
Kitchen cam, meet living room cam.

33:30.770 --> 33:33.510
Looks like a normal digital
picture frame, right?

33:33.510 --> 33:36.210
Except, see that little
pinhole right there?

33:36.210 --> 33:38.010
That's actually a camera.

33:38.010 --> 33:39.250
The best part?

33:39.250 --> 33:40.623
It's motion activated.

33:41.600 --> 33:44.400
Same deal with the one I'm
putting in Jacob's room.

33:44.400 --> 33:45.480
Jacob cam.

33:45.480 --> 33:48.010
So these new cameras will let me see

33:48.010 --> 33:50.530
what Jacob's up to when I'm not home.

33:50.530 --> 33:52.613
Okay, here we go.

33:55.131 --> 33:58.881
(Skype call on laptop rings)

34:00.850 --> 34:02.300
Hi Dr. Arden.

34:02.300 --> 34:05.163
I'm sorry, I completely
lost track of time.

34:05.163 --> 34:06.478
- No worries.

34:06.478 --> 34:07.470
You remember me?

34:07.470 --> 34:09.260
- Of course, yeah!

34:09.260 --> 34:13.790
- I watched that clip you
sent; that video from Jacob.

34:13.790 --> 34:16.010
When did this start?

34:16.010 --> 34:17.303
This behavior?

34:18.793 --> 34:20.949
- When he was a baby.

34:20.949 --> 34:22.389
An infant.

34:22.389 --> 34:24.639
He didn't like to be touched

34:24.639 --> 34:28.313
so he'd just lay there screaming at me.

34:28.313 --> 34:31.370
I mean, I was always his mom, you know?

34:31.370 --> 34:33.699
His hero, his protector,

34:33.699 --> 34:37.960
but by the time he was 14 I
didn't know who he was anymore.

34:37.960 --> 34:41.489
- I understand he received
counseling at the time.

34:41.489 --> 34:44.373
- He's been in counseling
since he was seven years old.

34:45.770 --> 34:49.070
He was drawing these disturbing pictures

34:49.920 --> 34:53.520
with this baby with this knife

34:53.520 --> 34:56.139
and, I don't know, some kind of bloodbath.

34:56.139 --> 34:58.720
- Your mother mentioned that, yeah...

34:58.720 --> 35:00.338
Do you remember the
pictures you used to draw

35:00.338 --> 35:02.653
when you were a young girl, Abbey?

35:05.350 --> 35:06.670
- No.

35:06.670 --> 35:09.760
- Yeah, your mother, she
didn't want them in the house.

35:09.760 --> 35:12.473
- I'm sorry...
- What's that?

35:12.473 --> 35:15.510
- I was kinda hoping we
could just talk about Jacob.

35:15.510 --> 35:17.200
- Of course, of course.

35:17.200 --> 35:20.823
Was he ever diagnosed as CU?

35:21.780 --> 35:24.453
Callous and unemotional traits?

35:25.520 --> 35:27.180
- No.

35:27.180 --> 35:30.050
- Has he ever been hospitalized.

35:30.050 --> 35:32.810
- No, he's pretty much outsmarted

35:32.810 --> 35:34.363
every therapist he's ever had.

35:35.420 --> 35:36.840
- Do you think Jacob

35:36.840 --> 35:39.863
is really capable of harming you, Abbey?

35:41.770 --> 35:42.603
- I don't know.

35:44.023 --> 35:46.855
I mean, I keep having this crazy dream

35:46.855 --> 35:49.660
where I'm standing on a stool

35:49.660 --> 35:51.260
in the middle of the living room

35:52.202 --> 35:54.580
and there's something around my neck.

35:54.580 --> 35:57.140
Like a rope, but not a rope.

35:57.140 --> 35:58.283
Smoother than a rope.

36:00.468 --> 36:03.560
I've wet myself, I know that sounds crazy,

36:03.560 --> 36:05.880
but my pajama bottoms are wet.

36:05.880 --> 36:07.013
They're itchy.

36:09.394 --> 36:12.423
- How did you get up on that stool?

36:13.700 --> 36:14.533
- I don't know.

36:14.533 --> 36:17.483
All I know is that something has happened.

36:18.360 --> 36:21.970
He's done something really really bad.

36:21.970 --> 36:23.610
- [Dr. Arden] Who?

36:23.610 --> 36:24.443
- Jacob.

36:28.405 --> 36:29.853
And he's giggling,

36:30.930 --> 36:33.500
laughing like he's
proud of what he's done;

36:33.500 --> 36:34.720
he's won, somehow.

36:34.720 --> 36:36.223
Like the joke's on me.

36:37.114 --> 36:40.623
I just kinda wanna step off the stool.

36:41.790 --> 36:43.100
- Do you?

36:43.100 --> 36:44.490
- What?

36:44.490 --> 36:45.610
Oh, no.

36:45.610 --> 36:46.443
No.

36:46.443 --> 36:49.453
- I'd like you to consider, for a moment,

36:50.750 --> 36:54.583
that it's not Jacob who
put you up on that stool.

36:55.680 --> 36:56.760
- What?

36:56.760 --> 36:58.500
I put myself up there?

36:58.500 --> 36:59.840
I wrapped a cord around my own neck

36:59.840 --> 37:02.210
and strung myself from the ceiling?

37:02.210 --> 37:04.930
- Is there any chance that in this dream

37:04.930 --> 37:08.523
it was Jerry who put you up on that stool?

37:09.610 --> 37:10.443
- Seriously?

37:12.228 --> 37:16.400
- I don't want to rule out
any possibilities, that's all.

37:16.400 --> 37:17.770
- I can't believe this is happening.

37:17.770 --> 37:19.156
Of course this is happening.

37:19.156 --> 37:23.930
- The fact that Jacob just
turned 16 is significant, Abbey.

37:23.930 --> 37:27.800
That's the same age
that Jerry was when he--

37:27.800 --> 37:30.777
- Yeah, you know what, I get it.

